   "source": [
    "# Spaceship Titanic Machine Learning Project — Reviewed and Coherent Version\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook builds a complete machine-learning workflow for the Kaggle **Spaceship Titanic** dataset. The objective is to predict whether each passenger was transported.\n",
    "\n",
    "The workflow is organised as follows:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Load libraries and data.\n",
    "2. Inspect the structure of the train and test datasets.\n",
    "3. Analyse the target variable.\n",
    "4. Analyse missing values.\n",
    "5. Explore numerical and categorical variables.\n",
    "6. Engineer new features from `PassengerId`, `Cabin`, spending variables, age, route and name.\n",
    "7. Check feature relationships with the target.\n",
    "8. Compare train and test distributions.\n",
    "9. Build preprocessing and modelling pipelines.\n",
    "10. Train baseline models.\n",
    "11. Tune the strongest models.\n",
    "12. Select the best model and create a Kaggle submission file.\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Important:** place `train.csv` and `test.csv` in the same folder as this notebook before running it.\n"
   ]
  },
