  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b1b34872",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 8 interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Age groups can capture non-linear age effects that a single numerical age column may miss. Spending behaviour is usually one of the strongest signals in this dataset: passengers with no spending are often much more likely to be transported, while passengers with higher service spending are often less likely to be transported."
   ]
  },
