   "source": [
    "### Step 10 interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Categorical variables are useful when different categories have clearly different transported rates. `CryoSleep` is normally one of the strongest original categorical variables. `HomePlanet` and `Destination` can also be informative. `VIP` is often weaker because the number of VIP passengers is small and the transported-rate difference is usually limited."
