   "source": [
    "### Step 11 interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "P-values indicate whether a relationship is statistically detectable, but they do not show practical strength. With almost 9,000 training rows, even weak relationships can have small p-values. For categorical variables, Cramér's V is more useful for strength. For numerical variables, compare both correlation direction and group means/medians. Spending variables with higher means among non-transported passengers are strong candidates for modelling."
   ]
