   "source": [
    "### Step 12 interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "This step makes the notebook coherent because all engineered columns used later are now created in one place. `Route` captures the combination of origin and destination. `DeckSide` captures the interaction between cabin deck and cabin side. Spending features convert several raw service columns into behaviour-based variables that are easier for models to use. The train and test sets are engineered together only for non-target-derived features such as group size and family size; the target is not used to create these features."
   ]
