  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0221f848",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 13 interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "The engineered spending features should be among the strongest signals. `NoSpend`, `SpendCount`, `log_TotalSpend_filled0`, and `log_LuxurySpend` are especially useful because they summarise passenger behaviour more clearly than the raw service columns. `Deck`, `Side`, `Route`, and `DeckSide` may also capture location or travel-pattern effects. `CabinKnown` is included for completeness, but it often has weak standalone value."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c9b2ebc4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 14 — Interaction heatmaps\n",
    "\n",
    "This step visualises combined categorical effects that may not be obvious when looking at one variable at a time."
   ]
