   "source": [
    "pivot_route = train_eda.pivot_table(\n",
    "    index=\"HomePlanet\",\n",
    "    columns=\"Destination\",\n",
    "    values=TARGET,\n",
    "    aggfunc=\"mean\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(pivot_route, annot=True, fmt=\".2f\", cmap=\"Blues\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Transported Rate: HomePlanet x Destination\")\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "pivot_deck_side = train_eda.pivot_table(\n",
    "    index=\"Deck\",\n",
    "    columns=\"Side\",\n",
    "    values=TARGET,\n",
    "    aggfunc=\"mean\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(pivot_deck_side, annot=True, fmt=\".2f\", cmap=\"Blues\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Transported Rate: Deck x Side\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "162a34cc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 14 interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "The heatmaps justify the engineered interaction features. If transported rates vary strongly by origin-destination pair, `Route` can help the model. If transported rates differ across deck and side combinations, `DeckSide` can add useful information beyond using `Deck` and `Side` separately."
   ]
  },
