   "source": [
    "### Step 21 interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Baseline models provide a reference point before tuning. Logistic regression is useful as a simple linear benchmark. Random Forest, Extra Trees and HistGradientBoosting can capture non-linear relationships and interactions. The best baseline model is the one with the strongest validation performance, but also compare balanced accuracy, precision, recall, F1 and ROC AUC to understand the type of errors each model makes."
