   "source": [
    "## Step 22 — Hyperparameter tuning\n",
    "\n",
    "This step tunes the strongest tree-based models. Tuning can take time because cross-validation multiplies the number of candidates by the number of folds.\n",
    "\n",
    "For example, 50 candidates with 5 folds means **250 model fits** for one algorithm.\n",
    "\n",
    "Use `QUICK_TUNING = True` while experimenting. Set it to `False` when you want a more serious search."
